─────────────────────────────────────────
INSTRUCTIONS
─────────────────────────────────────────
- Follow the System Message exactly.
- This layer exists to bind live state to the System Message, not to replace it.
- Prefer the shortest faithful reply that solves the current turn.

TURN BINDING
- Classify the newest inbound using PRIMARY MESSAGE TYPE above.

- FRESH GREETING CHECK (runs first): If FRESH GREETING HINT = true, apply the System Message FRESH THREAD GREETING RULE. Use customerFullName to detect the title (Pastor, Bishop, Rev, Apostle, Prophet, Elder, Deacon, Dr, Archbishop). Use countryName and isKenyaNumber to decide whether to include the country reference line. Ask the city question only if location is not already known. Do not push product. Output only the greeting + city ask.

- If PRIMARY MESSAGE TYPE = cart_complete or RECAP MODE HINT = order_summary: use ORDER SUMMARY format (mode 5 in System Message CART DISPLAY RULES). Display the full cart cleanly, show the total, then ask "Would you prefer delivery or pickup?" — nothing else.

- VESTMENT CHECK: Read VESTMENT ITEM HINT. If isVestment=true, follow this priority order:
  • needsBaseGarment=true (chasuble or cope): clarify "over a cassock set or an alb?" BEFORE anything else.
  • needsColour=true AND needsGender=true: ask colour/design and gender together. Include the office-holder context line on first discovery turn if role not stated.
  • needsColour=true only: ask colour/design.
  • needsGender=true only: ask gender.
  • needsAccessories=true: ask the accessory question appropriate to the item (see System Message VESTMENT DISCOVERY RULE for exact combinations per item type — cassock full-set vs single, alb accessories, gown + stole, etc.).
  • All checks pass (needsAccessories=false, everything settled): do NOT proactively ask "how many?". Acknowledge what is being built and invite the customer to state quantities naturally ("Let me know the quantities you'd like" / "What quantities would you like?").

- Then read: salesStage, lastAskedKey, previousQuestionAnswered, CURRENT CART, NEWLY ADDED THIS TURN, RECAP MODE HINT, and suggestedNextAction.
- Read COMMERCIAL INTELLIGENCE before drafting. Use nextMove as the recommended reply mode. Use answerDebtExists and answerDebtTopic to check whether a direct question is still open — answer that first.
- Read MOOD SIGNALS before choosing tone. Adjust length and warmth using responseWeight, patience, urgency, and directness.
- Use trustTemperature: if "needs_reassurance" lead with one short reassuring line; if "under_strain" reply shorter and skip the upsell.
- Use customerPriority to front-load what the customer cares about most.
- Treat short affirmative replies according to `known.oneQuestionKey` and current stage.
- Only treat "yes" as order confirmation if the last unresolved key or current stage indicates order_confirmation.
- If the newest message was OUTBOUND, return no customer-facing text and output only:
<CONTROL>{"nextAction":"await"}</CONTROL>

CART AUTHORITY RULE
- CURRENT CART is the authoritative source of truth.
- Render the order from context.cart.cart_items / context.cart.full_cart.
- NEVER rebuild the cart from prior outbound text.
- NEVER treat NEWLY ADDED THIS TURN as the full order unless no full cart exists at all.
- Use items_added as delta only.

RECAP SELECTION RULE
- Use RECAP MODE HINT as the default:
  – none → no cart recap
  – micro → one-line order reminder only if useful
  – update → acknowledge the change, then updated subtotal, then one next step
  – full_checkout → render the full cart cleanly from CURRENT CART
- Do not use full recap every turn.
- If nothing material changed, do not paste a full order again unless the customer asked.

PRICE RULE
- Use displayCurrency from GEOGRAPHY & CURRENCY above.
- Never mix currencies.
- Use prices from MATCHED PRODUCTS FROM CATALOG first.
- Use System Message fallback prices only if a product is missing from MATCHED PRODUCTS.

OUT-OF-STOCK / OUT-OF-CATALOG / PENDING RULE
- Every unavailable item in CURRENT CART must remain visible in the order summary.
- Do not show KES 0 or $0 for unavailable items. Use "— not currently in stock".
- Pending-quote items stay visible as pending and remain outside subtotal.
- Subtotal includes only available, billable items.
- Mention unavailable or pending items briefly once when relevant. Do not repeat each turn.

IMAGE-TO-CART EXECUTION RULE
- Use `context.vision` first. Use `context.image` only as fallback.
1) inquiry_only → identify + answer; do not add to cart
2) soft_buy → if imageBundleMatched=true and strong, treat bundle as qty 1; else use imageAutoAddCandidates
3) explicit_buy_with_qty → use bundle or auto-add candidates with stated qty
4) buy_qty_missing → identify item; do not add yet; ask qty
5) compare_or_clarify → identify / compare; do not add yet
- Never add imageConfirmCandidates silently. Ask only if that is the single next blocking detail.
- Never add items listed in imageDoNotAutoAdd.
- Do not describe the full image unless asked.

COMMERCIAL INTELLIGENCE RULE
- answerDebtExists=true → answer that question first before any close or upsell.
- closeReadiness=high → move toward the next gate (confirmation, payment, dispatch).
- closeReadiness=medium → continue the buying flow naturally without hard-closing.
- closeReadiness=low → answer, clarify, or reassure first.
- responseWeight=very_short → maximum 1–2 sentences.
- responseWeight=short → standard reply length.
- responseWeight=medium → allowed to explain if checkout clarity genuinely needs it.
- designStrictness=high → confirm exact design / colour / finish before cart or payment step.
- logisticsSensitivity=high → address shipping / packing / protection before closing.

MOOD CALIBRATION RULE
- patience=low → shorter replies, resolve quickly, skip extra context.
- urgency=high → answer the urgent point immediately; skip all preamble.
- directness=high → match blunt/direct tone; skip softeners.
- energy=low → keep reply brief; do not burden with long text.
- questionCount > 1 → address all questions before asking a new one.

MESSAGE-TYPE BEHAVIOUR
- fresh_greeting (FRESH GREETING HINT=true, no prior outbound): apply FRESH THREAD GREETING RULE from System Message; use customerFullName for title detection; include country reference line for non-Kenya numbers; ask city question only; no product push
- greeting_only: reply simply and warmly; do not push product, payment, delivery, or closing flow
- email_only: acknowledge briefly; only ask whether to use it for receipt if payment stage is active
- acknowledgement_only: reply briefly; do not restart the sales flow
- defer_or_later: acknowledge kindly; do not push payment or immediate confirmation
- objection_or_value_resistance: defend value calmly before any close; offer one helpful path only if natural
- decision_ready: move according to lastAskedKey, known.oneQuestionKey, and current stage
- product_discovery / price_question for a VESTMENT item (isVestment=true): confirm the item; for chasuble/cope — clarify base garment (cassock set or alb) FIRST; apply VESTMENT DISCOVERY RULE — colour/design → gender → accessories; include office-holder context line on first discovery turn if role not stated; do NOT proactively ask "how many?" after accessories — invite the customer to state quantities
- order_progress / product_discovery / business_question (non-vestment): answer the real need first, then move one stage only
- non_buying_out_of_scope: steer back briefly; if nonBuyingCount >= 2, prepare for short pause-style close

QUESTION DISCIPLINE
- Ask only one blocking question when needed.
- Never ask a question already answered unless the answer became invalid because the order changed.
- Do not ask delivery method twice if still valid.
- Do not ask payment method twice if already selected.
- Do not ask receipt name too early.
- Do not ask two commercial questions in one reply.

LEAST-TO-MOST
item → (vestment: overlay-base if chasuble/cope → colour → gender → accessories → customer-led qty) / (non-vestment: customer-led qty) → anything else → country-aware shipping (Kenya: delivery/pickup; International: courier options) → location/area → order confirmation → payment method → receipt name → payment proof

CONFIRMATION RULE
- Respect ORDER GATE exactly.
- Do not treat browsing, pricing, or adding items as final order confirmation.
- If isDuplicateOrder=true, do not place again; explain briefly and ask whether to add, change, or keep it.

CLARIFICATION-PRESERVES-CART RULE
- If clarificationRequired=true, preserve the existing full cart.
- Do not render the order as empty unless the cart is truly empty.
- Block only the ambiguous latest addition.
- Ask only the clarification question.

NAME / RECEIPT RULE
- Use CUSTOMER ON FILE first.
- If the name is already known and reliable, do not ask again.
- Only ask for receipt name in payment stage if still needed.
- If the customer shared only an email and payment stage is not active, just acknowledge it.

MOOD RULE
- Reassure briefly if concerned or cautious.
- Stay practical if neutral.
- Be warm without becoming long.
- Respect emoji limits from the System Message.

SHIPPING / GEO RULE
- Read COUNTRY / GEO only from provided state. Do not invent route, city, or country.
- countryCode=254 (Kenya):
  • Transition from ORDER SUMMARY: "Would you prefer delivery or pickup?"
  • Delivery: ask area; quote KES 350 as indicative ("I'll confirm the exact amount for your location").
  • Pickup: share Nairobi pickup details; same-day dispatch if paid by 18:00 EAT.
- countryCode≠254 (International):
  • Do NOT ask "delivery or pickup?". Do NOT suggest pickup unprompted.
  • Present courier options: "We ship from Nairobi via DHL, EMS/Posta, and a few other couriers. The cost depends on the courier, the weight of the parcel, and how fast you need it. How would you like us to ship?"
  • Mention pickup ONLY if the customer says they have someone to collect on their behalf.
  • Do not share the Nairobi pickup address unless the customer asks OR has arranged pickup.
  • Do not use Kenya local fee language (KES 300/350/400) for international customers.

PAYMENT RULE
- Apply payment routing from the System Message by countryCode.
- Never default to Kenya Paybill for international numbers.
- If selectedPaymentMethod is already set, send only that method.
- If paymentDetailsSent=true and awaitingPaymentProof=true, ask for proof only.

SMART SELLING RULE
answer first → reassure if needed → recommend if useful → micro-close if appropriate
Never upsell before the base need is clear.
Offer at most one add-on, once only.

STYLE RULE
- Do not narrate internal processing.
- Prefer direct sales phrasing over assistant phrasing.
- Avoid padded intros. Avoid repeating settled facts.

LENGTH RULE
- Let the turn decide the reply budget:
  – acknowledgement / greeting → very short
  – micro recap → short
  – update recap → medium
  – payment / full checkout → longer only if needed

FINAL RULE
- End with zero or one question on its own line only if needed.
- Append exactly one control line as the final line:
<CONTROL>{"nextAction":"reply"}</CONTROL>
or
<CONTROL>{"nextAction":"await"}</CONTROL>
or
<CONTROL>{"nextAction":"orderCheck"}</CONTROL>

─────────────────────────────────────────
OUTPUT
─────────────────────────────────────────
Return the final customer-facing message followed by the final control line:
<CONTROL>{"nextAction":"reply" | "await" | "orderCheck"}</CONTROL>

parameters.jsCode:
// --- echo-merge-key ---
// Purpose: Extract control line (<CONTROL>{"nextAction": "...", ...}</CONTROL>),
// sanitize visible text, and safely set context.nextAction while preserving all fields.
// Supports nextAction: "reply" | "await" | "orderCheck" | "orderPlaced"
//
// Additions vs original:
//   - Fix 2: Explicit order confirmation gate (blocks orderPlaced unless customer confirmed)
//   - Fix 1: Ambiguity passthrough (blocks orderPlaced if clarification still required)
//   - Preserves requiresClarification, customerExplicitlyConfirmed, ambiguity from parse_analyse

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 0) HELPERS
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const toStr = (v) => (v == null ? "" : String(v));

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 1) RAW MODEL OUTPUT
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const raw =
  toStr($json.output)      ||
  toStr($json.reply_text)  ||
  toStr($json.text);

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 2) PULL CONTROL BLOCK (never throw)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

let control = {};
try {
  const m = raw.match(/<CONTROL>\s*({[\s\S]*?})\s*<\/CONTROL>/i);
  if (m && m[1]) control = JSON.parse(m[1]);
} catch (e) {
  // swallow parse error; control stays {}
}

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 3) CLEAN CUSTOMER-FACING TEXT
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

let clean = raw
  .replace(/<CONTROL>[\s\S]*?<\/CONTROL>/gi, "")
  .replace(/^\s*<[^>]+>\s*$/gmi, "")
  .replace(/^\s*set_next_action\s*\([\s\S]*?\)\s*$/gmi, "")
  .replace(/\n{3,}/g, "\n\n")
  .trim();

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 4) RESOLVE NEXT ACTION (raw, before gates)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const rawNextAction =
  (typeof control.nextAction === "string" && control.nextAction) ||
  (typeof $json.context?.nextAction === "string" && $json.context.nextAction) ||
  "reply";

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 5) EXPLICIT CONFIRMATION GATE (Fix 2)
// Blocks orderPlaced unless the customer sent a clear affirmative this turn.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const CONFIRM_PHRASES = /\b(yes|yeah|yep|yap|sure|ok|okay|confirm(?:ed)?|proceed|go\s+ahead|place(?: the)? order|place it|send it|i(?:'m| am) ready|ndio|sawa|endelea)\b/i;

// Read confirmation state from parse_analyse output (preferred — already computed)
// Fall back to re-checking the latest inbound text if not stamped
const customerExplicitlyConfirmed =
  $json.customerExplicitlyConfirmed === true ||
  CONFIRM_PHRASES.test(
    toStr(
      $json.context?.lastText_inbound  ||
      $json.context?.lastInbound?.text ||
      ""
    )
  );

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 6) AMBIGUITY GATE (Fix 1)
// Blocks orderPlaced if item clarification is still pending.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const requiresClarification =
  $json.requiresClarification === true ||
  $json.context?.known?.oneQuestionKey === "item_clarification";

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 7) APPLY GATES — compute safe nextAction
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const nextAction = (() => {
  // Never place an order when item is still ambiguous
  if (requiresClarification) return "reply";

  // Never place an order without explicit customer confirmation
  if (rawNextAction === "orderPlaced" && !customerExplicitlyConfirmed) return "reply";

  return rawNextAction;
})();

const isOrderPlaced = nextAction === "orderPlaced";

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 8) HANDLE orderPlaced — extract order summary from control block
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

let confirmedItems    = null;
let confirmedSubtotal = null;
let confirmedName     = null;
let confirmedPhone    = null;

if (isOrderPlaced) {
  // Items array from control line
  if (Array.isArray(control.items) && control.items.length) {
    confirmedItems = control.items.map((i) => ({
      name:  String(i.name  || ""),
      qty:   Number(i.qty   || 0),
      unit:  Number(i.unit  || 0),
      total: Number(i.total || 0),
      sku:   i.sku || null,
    }));
  }

  // Subtotal
  if (control.subtotal != null && !isNaN(Number(control.subtotal))) {
    confirmedSubtotal = Number(control.subtotal);
  }
  // Fall back to computing from items if not provided
  if (confirmedSubtotal == null && Array.isArray(confirmedItems)) {
    confirmedSubtotal = confirmedItems.reduce(
      (s, i) => s + (i.total || i.qty * i.unit || 0), 0
    );
  }

  // Name & phone — prefer control line, fall back to context
  confirmedName  = control.name  || $json.context?.confirm?.nameCandidate  || null;
  confirmedPhone = control.phone || $json.context?.confirm?.phoneCandidate  || $json.wa_id || null;
}

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 9) OPTIONAL PASSTHROUGHS
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const statePatch = (control && typeof control.statePatch === "object") ? control.statePatch : null;
const telemetry  = (control && control.telemetry  != null)             ? control.telemetry  : null;

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 10) PRESERVE wa_id
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const wa_id_here =
  $json.wa_id            ||
  $json.context?.wa_id   ||
  $json.patch?.wa_id     ||
  null;

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 11) BUILD RESULT — preserve all incoming fields
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const out = {
  ...$json,
  reply_text: clean,
  output:     clean,

  context: {
    ...($json.context || {}),
    ...(wa_id_here ? { wa_id: wa_id_here } : {}),
    nextAction,
    ...(statePatch ? { statePatch } : {}),
    ...(telemetry  ? { telemetry }  : {}),
    // Preserve ambiguity state in context so Compose context / prompts can read it
    known: {
      ...($json.context?.known || {}),
      // Keep itemCandidates / ambiguousRoot / clarificationQuestion if they exist
      ...(requiresClarification ? {
        oneQuestionKey:       "item_clarification",
        itemCandidates:       $json.context?.known?.itemCandidates      || $json.ambiguity?.candidates    || [],
        ambiguousRoot:        $json.context?.known?.ambiguousRoot       || $json.ambiguity?.ambiguousRoot || "",
        clarificationQuestion:$json.context?.known?.clarificationQuestion || $json.ambiguity?.clarificationQuestion || "",
      } : {}),
    },
  },

  ...(statePatch ? { statePatch } : {}),
  ...(telemetry  ? { telemetry }  : {}),

  // ── Gate state — surfaced for Post-process and downstream ──
  customerExplicitlyConfirmed,
  requiresClarification,

  mergeKey: 1,
};

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 12) STAMP orderPlaced / order_status
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

if (isOrderPlaced) {
  out.orderPlaced  = true;
  out.order_status = "pending";
  if (confirmedItems)              out.confirmed_items    = confirmedItems;
  if (confirmedSubtotal != null)   out.confirmed_subtotal = confirmedSubtotal;
  if (confirmedName)               out.confirmed_name     = confirmedName;
  if (confirmedPhone)              out.confirmed_phone    = confirmedPhone;
} else {
  // Explicitly false so Post-process can check without undefined risk
  out.orderPlaced  = false;
  out.order_status = $json.order_status || "open";

  // If we downgraded from orderPlaced due to missing confirmation,
  // stamp a flag so NEEMA knows to ask for confirmation next turn
  if (rawNextAction === "orderPlaced" && !customerExplicitlyConfirmed && !requiresClarification) {
    out.awaitingOrderConfirmation = true;
  } else {
    out.awaitingOrderConfirmation = false;
  }
}

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// 13) ROOT wa_id
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

if (wa_id_here) out.wa_id = wa_id_here;

return [out];

// Post-process (Combined "AI Items Bridge" + "Post-process")
// - Dynamic pricing from DB catalog API (flat JSON) + Firestore fallback
// - Text → items parsing covering full product range
// - Unify reply, compute lastSeen, routing, and stable order_event seeding
// - Handles orderPlaced signal from echo-merge-key
// - Fix 1/D: Blocks all item parsing when requiresClarification = true
// - Fix 1/C: candidateLists rejects KES 0 ghost items from upstream
// - Fix 2:   Blocks orderPlaced unless customerExplicitlyConfirmed = true
// - Fix 3:   Duplicate order detection — prevents re-placing identical open orders
// - Preserve ALL upstream fields, return SINGLE-ITEM ARRAY, mergeKey:1

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// HELPERS
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const num = (v, d = 0) => {
  const n = Number(v);
  return Number.isFinite(n) ? n : d;
};
const toLower = (s) => String(s || "").toLowerCase().trim();
const nowIso  = () => new Date().toISOString();

/** Firestore typed unwrap (map/array aware) **/
function unwrap(v) {
  if (v == null) return null;
  if (typeof v !== "object") return v;
  if ("stringValue"    in v) return v.stringValue;
  if ("integerValue"   in v) return Number(v.integerValue);
  if ("doubleValue"    in v) return Number(v.doubleValue);
  if ("booleanValue"   in v) return !!v.booleanValue;
  if ("timestampValue" in v) return v.timestampValue;
  if (v.mapValue?.fields) {
    const o = {};
    for (const k of Object.keys(v.mapValue.fields)) o[k] = unwrap(v.mapValue.fields[k]);
    return o;
  }
  if (Array.isArray(v.arrayValue?.values)) return v.arrayValue.values.map(unwrap);
  return v;
}

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// INPUT
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const input  = $json || {};
const ctx    = input.context || {};
const fields = input.fields  || {};
const msgs   = Array.isArray(input.messages) ? input.messages : [];

// ── Gate signals from echo-merge-key / parse_analyse ────────
// These are the single source of truth for all three fixes.
const requiresClarification       = input.requiresClarification === true ||
  ctx.known?.oneQuestionKey === "item_clarification";

const customerExplicitlyConfirmed = input.customerExplicitlyConfirmed === true;
const awaitingOrderConfirmation   = input.awaitingOrderConfirmation   === true;

// ── orderPlaced: double-checked safety net ───────────────────
// echo-merge-key already downgraded this when gates failed,
// but we re-verify here so Post-process is self-contained.
const isOrderPlaced =
  input.orderPlaced === true &&
  customerExplicitlyConfirmed  &&
  !requiresClarification;

const orderStatusInput = isOrderPlaced ? "pending" : (input.order_status || "open");

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// BUILD CATALOG PRICE MAP
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const catalogFlat =
  Array.isArray(input.catalog) &&
  input.catalog.length &&
  input.catalog[0]?.sku !== undefined
    ? input.catalog
    : null;

let catalogDocs = null;
if (!catalogFlat) {
  const possibleArrays = Object.values(input).filter(
    (v) => Array.isArray(v) && v.length && v[0] && typeof v[0] === "object"
  );
  for (const arr of possibleArrays) {
    if (arr[0].sku !== undefined && typeof arr[0].price === "number") {
      Object.defineProperty(input, "_catalogFlatFound", { value: arr });
      break;
    }
    if (arr[0].document || arr[0].name === "readTime") {
      catalogDocs = arr;
      break;
    }
  }
}

const effectiveCatalogFlat = catalogFlat || input._catalogFlatFound || null;
const priceMap = {};

// DB API flat format (preferred)
if (Array.isArray(effectiveCatalogFlat)) {
  for (const item of effectiveCatalogFlat) {
    const name    = String(item.name  || "");
    const sku     = String(item.sku   || "");
    const unit    = num(item.price, 0);
    const aliases = Array.isArray(item.aliases) ? item.aliases : [];
    const baseKey = toLower(name);
    if (name && unit > 0) {
      priceMap[baseKey] = { name, sku, unit };
      for (const a of aliases) {
        const k = toLower(a);
        if (k && !priceMap[k]) priceMap[k] = { name, sku, unit };
      }
    }
  }
}

// Firestore format (legacy fallback)
if (Array.isArray(catalogDocs) && Object.keys(priceMap).length === 0) {
  for (const row of catalogDocs) {
    const doc = row.document || null;
    if (!doc?.fields) continue;
    const f       = doc.fields;
    const name    = unwrap(f.name)    || "";
    const sku     = unwrap(f.sku)     || "";
    const unit    = num(unwrap(f.price), 0);
    const aliases = unwrap(f.aliases) || [];
    const baseKey = toLower(name);
    if (name && unit > 0) {
      priceMap[baseKey] = { name, sku, unit };
      if (Array.isArray(aliases)) {
        for (const a of aliases) {
          const k = toLower(a);
          if (k && !priceMap[k]) priceMap[k] = { name, sku, unit };
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

// Hardcoded fallback
const fallbackMap = {
  "holy communion wafers (500 pcs)": { name: "Holy Communion Wafers (500 pcs)",        unit: 850,   sku: "WAFER-500"       },
  "500pcs":                           { name: "Holy Communion Wafers (500 pcs)",        unit: 850,   sku: "WAFER-500"       },
  "wafers":                           { name: "Holy Communion Wafers (500 pcs)",        unit: 850,   sku: "WAFER-500"       },
  "devai (1l non-alcoholic wine)":    { name: "Devai (1L non-alcoholic wine)",          unit: 800,   sku: "DEVAI-1L"        },
  "devai":                            { name: "Devai (1L non-alcoholic wine)",          unit: 800,   sku: "DEVAI-1L"        },
  "altar wine 750 ml":                { name: "Altar Wine (750ml)",                     unit: 1800,  sku: "ALTAR-750"       },
  "altarwine":                        { name: "Altar Wine (750ml)",                     unit: 1800,  sku: "ALTAR-750"       },
  "silver communion tray (40-cup)":   { name: "Silver Communion Tray 40-Cup (no lid)", unit: 13000, sku: "TRAY-40"         },
  "silver tray":                      { name: "Silver Communion Tray 40-Cup (no lid)", unit: 13000, sku: "TRAY-40"         },
  "devai prefilled cups":             { name: "Devai Prefilled Communion Cups (25 pcs)",unit: 750,  sku: "DEVAI-25"        },
  "aluminium tray":                   { name: "Aluminium Communion Tray 40-Cup",        unit: 7000,  sku: "TRAY-ALU"        },
  "gold tray":                        { name: "Gold Communion Tray 40-Cup (with lid)", unit: 23000, sku: "TRAY-GOLD-LID"   },
  "clerical shirt":                   { name: "Clerical Shirt (Normal Collar)",         unit: 2200,  sku: "SHIRT-NORM"      },
  "bishop shirt":                     { name: "Bishop Shirt (includes 19\" collar)",   unit: 4000,  sku: "SHIRT-BISH"      },
  "collar":                           { name: "Clerical Collar 8\"",                   unit: 350,   sku: "COLLAR-8"        },
  "anointing oil":                    { name: "Eliad Anointing Oil (750ml)",            unit: 5000,  sku: "OIL-ELIAD-750"   },
  "eliad":                            { name: "Eliad Anointing Oil (750ml)",            unit: 5000,  sku: "OIL-ELIAD-750"   },
  "efrat":                            { name: "Efrat Communion Wine (1L)",              unit: 3000,  sku: "EFRAT-1L"        },
};

function lookupUnit(aliasOrName) {
  const key = toLower(aliasOrName);
  if (priceMap[key])    return priceMap[key];
  if (fallbackMap[key]) return fallbackMap[key];
  return null;
}

const catalogSource = effectiveCatalogFlat
  ? `DB API (${Object.keys(priceMap).length} entries)`
  : catalogDocs
    ? `Firestore (${Object.keys(priceMap).length} entries)`
    : "hardcoded fallback";

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// TEXT → ITEMS PARSING
// Skipped entirely when requiresClarification = true.
// An ambiguous term (e.g. "cups") must not generate any
// item line — the customer has not yet chosen the product.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const rawText =
  ctx.lastText_inbound ||
  input.text           ||
  input.msgText        ||
  input.reply_text     ||
  input.output         ||
  "";

const text = toLower(rawText);

function qtyNear(word, fallback = 1) {
  const rx1 = new RegExp(`(\\d+)\\s*(?:${word})`, "i");
  const rx2 = new RegExp(`(?:${word})\\s*(\\d+)`, "i");
  const m1  = text.match(rx1);
  const m2  = text.match(rx2);
  if (m1 && m1[1]) return num(m1[1], fallback);
  if (m2 && m2[1]) return num(m2[1], fallback);
  return fallback;
}

const parsedItems = [];

function pushItem(lookupKey, fallbackName, wordPattern) {
  const ref  = lookupUnit(lookupKey);
  const unit = ref?.unit ?? 0;
  const q    = qtyNear(wordPattern, 1);
  parsedItems.push({
    name:  ref?.name || fallbackName,
    sku:   ref?.sku  || null,
    qty:   q,
    unit,
    total: q * unit,
  });
}

if (!requiresClarification) {

  // Wafers
  if (/\b(wafer|wafers|hosts?|eucharist)\b/.test(text)) {
    const size =
      /1[,\s]?000\s*pcs|1000\s*pcs/.test(text) ? "1000" :
      /500\s*pcs|500pcs/.test(text)             ? "500"  :
      /250\s*pcs/.test(text)                    ? "250"  :
      /150\s*pcs/.test(text)                    ? "150"  : "500";
    pushItem(
      `holy communion wafers (${size} pcs)`,
      `Holy Communion Wafers (${size} pcs)`,
      "(?:pack(?:et)?s?|pcs|pieces|wafer|wafers|host|hosts)"
    );
  }

  // Disposable cups — only when not ambiguous
  // (devai / prefilled already disambiguated by parse_analyse)
  if (/\bcups?\b/.test(text) && /\b(disposable|plastic)\b/.test(text)) {
    const qty =
      /2[,\s]?500/.test(text) ? 2500 :
      /1[,\s]?000/.test(text) ? 1000 :
      /500/.test(text)         ? 500  :
      /250/.test(text)         ? 250  : 50;
    pushItem(
      `disposable communion cups (${qty} pcs)`,
      `Disposable Communion Cups (${qty} pcs)`,
      "(?:cup|cups|pcs|pieces)"
    );
  }

  // Devai prefilled cups — specific enough, no ambiguity
  if (/\bdevai\b/.test(text) && /\b(prefilled|prefill|cup|cups)\b/.test(text)) {
    pushItem(
      "devai prefilled communion cups (25 pcs)",
      "Devai Prefilled Communion Cups (25 pcs)",
      "(?:devai|cup|cups|pack|pcs)"
    );
  }

  // Devai wine — only when cups not mentioned
  if (/\bdevai\b/.test(text) && !/\b(prefilled|prefill|cup|cups)\b/.test(text)) {
    pushItem(
      "devai non-alcoholic communion wine (1l)",
      "Devai Non-Alcoholic Communion Wine (1L)",
      "(?:devai|bottle|bottles|ltr|liter|litre)"
    );
  }

  // Altar wine — specific term, unambiguous
  if (/\baltar\s*wine\b|\baltarwine\b/.test(text)) {
    pushItem(
      "altar wine (750ml)",
      "Altar Wine (750ml)",
      "(?:altar\\s*wine|altarwine|bottle|bottles)"
    );
  }

  // Efrat wine — specific term, unambiguous
  if (/\befrat\b/.test(text)) {
    pushItem(
      "efrat communion wine (1l)",
      "Efrat Communion Wine (1L)",
      "(?:efrat|bottle|bottles)"
    );
  }

  // Trays — only when material/colour is specified
  // Plain "tray" alone is caught by parse_analyse ambiguity
  if (/\btrays?\b/.test(text)) {
    if (/\bgold\b/.test(text)) {
      const withLid = /\bwith\s*lid\b/.test(text);
      pushItem(
        withLid ? "gold communion tray 40-cup (with lid)" : "gold communion tray 40-cup (no lid)",
        withLid ? "Gold Communion Tray 40-Cup (with lid)" : "Gold Communion Tray 40-Cup (no lid)",
        "(?:tray|trays|gold)"
      );
    } else if (/\bsilver\b/.test(text)) {
      const withLid = /\bwith\s*lid\b/.test(text);
      pushItem(
        withLid ? "silver communion tray 40-cup (with lid)" : "silver communion tray 40-cup (no lid)",
        withLid ? "Silver Communion Tray 40-Cup (with lid)" : "Silver Communion Tray 40-Cup (no lid)",
        "(?:tray|trays|silver)"
      );
    } else if (/\balumini?um\b/.test(text)) {
      pushItem(
        "aluminium communion tray 40-cup",
        "Aluminium Communion Tray 40-Cup",
        "(?:tray|trays|alumini?um)"
      );
    } else if (/\bwood(?:en)?\b/.test(text)) {
      pushItem(
        "wooden communion tray 100-cup",
        "Wooden Communion Tray 100-Cup",
        "(?:tray|trays|wood(?:en)?)"
      );
    }
    // No else — plain "tray" alone is ambiguous and blocked by
    // requiresClarification before we reach this point
  }

  // Bread plates
  if (/\bbread\s*plate\b/.test(text)) {
    const isGold = /\bgold\b/.test(text);
    pushItem(
      isGold ? "gold bread plate" : "silver bread plate",
      isGold ? "Gold Bread Plate" : "Silver Bread Plate",
      "(?:plate|plates)"
    );
  }

  // Anointing oil
  if (/\banointing\s*oil\b|\beliad\b/.test(text)) {
    pushItem(
      "eliad anointing oil (750ml)",
      "Eliad Anointing Oil (750ml)",
      "(?:oil|bottle|bottles)"
    );
  }

  // Refill bottles
  if (/\brefill\s*bottle\b|\bspeed\s*bottle\b|\bpouring\s*flask\b/.test(text)) {
    const isLitre = /\b1\s*l\b|\b1\s*liter\b|\b1\s*litre\b/.test(text);
    pushItem(
      isLitre ? "communion refill bottle (1l)"   : "communion refill bottle (500ml)",
      isLitre ? "Communion Refill Bottle (1L)"   : "Communion Refill Bottle (500ml)",
      "(?:bottle|bottles|flask)"
    );
  }

  // Clerical shirts — only when type is specified
  if (/\bshirts?\b/.test(text) && !/\bt-shirt\b/.test(text)) {
    if (/\bbishop\b/.test(text)) {
      pushItem(
        "bishop shirt (includes 19\" collar)",
        "Bishop Shirt (includes 19\" collar)",
        "(?:shirt|shirts|pcs|units)"
      );
    } else if (/\b(normal|clerical)\b/.test(text)) {
      pushItem(
        "clerical shirt (normal collar)",
        "Clerical Shirt (Normal Collar)",
        "(?:shirt|shirts|pcs|units)"
      );
    }
    // Plain "shirt" alone is ambiguous — blocked by requiresClarification
  }

  // Collars — only when size is specified
  if (/\bcollars?\b/.test(text)) {
    const sizeMatch = text.match(/\b(8|10|12|14|17|19|21)\s*(?:inch|in|"|'')?(?:\s|$)/);
    if (sizeMatch) {
      const size = sizeMatch[1];
      pushItem(
        `clerical collar ${size}"`,
        `Clerical Collar ${size}"`,
        "(?:collar|collars|pcs|units)"
      );
    }
    // No size = ambiguous — blocked by requiresClarification
  }

  // Vestments
  const vestmentMap = {
    "cassock":    ["cassock",         "VEST-CASSOCK"    ],
    "ordination": ["Ordination Gown", "VEST-ORDINATION" ],
    "chasuble":   ["Chasuble",        "VEST-CHASUBLE"   ],
    "\\balb\\b":  ["Alb",             "VEST-ALB"        ],
    "stole":      ["Stole",           "VEST-STOLE"      ],
    "mitre":      ["Mitre",           "VEST-MITRE"      ],
  };
  for (const [pattern, [fallbackName, fallbackSku]] of Object.entries(vestmentMap)) {
    if (new RegExp(pattern, "i").test(text)) {
      const ref  = lookupUnit(toLower(fallbackName));
      const unit = ref?.unit ?? 0;
      parsedItems.push({
        name:  ref?.name || fallbackName,
        sku:   ref?.sku  || fallbackSku,
        qty:   1,
        unit,
        total: unit,
      });
    }
  }

} // end if (!requiresClarification)

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// REPLY TEXT
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const reply = input.reply_text || input.output ||
  "I'm here to help. What would you like to order today?";
const out = {
  ...input,
  reply_text:      String(reply).trim(),
  direction:       "outbound",
  _catalogSource:  catalogSource,
};

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// LATEST INBOUND SELECTION
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

function lastByTs(list) {
  if (!list?.length) return null;
  return list.slice().sort((a, b) =>
    (a.tsMs ?? Date.parse(a.tsIso || 0)) -
    (b.tsMs ?? Date.parse(b.tsIso || 0))
  ).pop();
}

const lastInboundFromContext = ctx.lastInbound || null;
const lastFromMessages       = lastByTs(msgs);
const lastTopLevel           = (input.tsMs || input.tsIso || input.text)
  ? { tsMs: input.tsMs, tsIso: input.tsIso, text: input.text,
      direction: input.direction || "inbound", wa_id: input.wa_id }
  : null;
const fieldsUnwrapped = fields && typeof fields === "object"
  ? unwrap({ mapValue: { fields } })
  : null;

const pick = (obj, key, fallback = null) =>
  (obj && obj[key] != null && String(obj[key]).length ? obj[key] : fallback);

const safeNode = (name) => {
  try { return $node[name]?.json || null; } catch { return null; }
};

const baseLast = lastInboundFromContext || lastTopLevel || lastFromMessages || fieldsUnwrapped || {};

const wa_id = pick(baseLast, "wa_id",
  ctx.wa_id                                     ||
  input.wa_id                                   ||
  input.patch?.wa_id                            ||
  fieldsUnwrapped?.wa_id                        ||
  safeNode("Merge compose+payload")?.wa_id      ||
  safeNode("echo-merge-key")?.wa_id             ||
  safeNode("Build Session Vars")?.wa_id         ||
  safeNode("Extract Sender ID")?.wa_id          ||
  safeNode("Gate after Touch")?.wa_id           ||
  safeNode("Normalize context")?.context?.wa_id ||
  ""
) || "";

const tsMs  = num(pick(baseLast, "tsMs", fieldsUnwrapped?.lastMessageTs), null);
const tsIso = pick(baseLast, "tsIso",
  fieldsUnwrapped?.lastMessageAtIso ||
  (tsMs != null ? new Date(tsMs).toISOString() : null)
);
const ltext = pick(baseLast, "text",
  ctx.lastText_inbound || input.msgText || input.text || ""
);
const ldir  = pick(baseLast, "direction",
  ctx.lastDirection || fieldsUnwrapped?.lastDirection || "inbound"
);

// ── wa_id guard ──────────────────────────
if (!wa_id || String(wa_id).trim() === "") {
  return [{
    ...input,
    wa_id:          "",
    _guard_skipped: true,
    _guard_reason:  "wa_id missing from all sources — check Get Catalog API node wiring",
    mergeKey:       1,
  }];
}

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// LAST SEEN + RETURN GAP
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

let seenGapMinutes = null;
if (tsIso) {
  const t = Date.parse(tsIso);
  if (!Number.isNaN(t)) seenGapMinutes = Math.round((Date.now() - t) / 60000);
} else if (tsMs != null) {
  seenGapMinutes = Math.round((Date.now() - Number(tsMs)) / 60000);
}
const isReturning = seenGapMinutes != null && seenGapMinutes > 60;

out.lastSeen = {
  wa_id,
  lastMessageAtIso: tsIso,
  lastMessageTs:    tsMs,
  lastText:         ltext,
  lastDirection:    ldir,
  state: ctx.state || { active: "active", cart: { items: [], subtotal: 0 } },
};
out.seenGapMinutes = seenGapMinutes;
out.isReturning    = isReturning;

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// ITEMS SELECTION (Fix C)
// candidateLists:
//   - Empty when clarification is pending (no ambiguous items allowed)
//   - Rejects upstream items_added entries where unit = 0 (KES 0 ghost items)
//   - Falls through to parsedItems which also produced nothing when
//     requiresClarification was true
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const upstreamItemsClean =
  Array.isArray(input.items_added) &&
  input.items_added.length > 0 &&
  input.items_added.every(i => num(i.unit, 0) > 0 || num(i.price, 0) > 0)
    ? input.items_added
    : null;

const candidateLists = requiresClarification ? [] : [
  isOrderPlaced && Array.isArray(input.confirmed_items) && input.confirmed_items.length
    ? input.confirmed_items : null,
  upstreamItemsClean,
  input.itemsToAdd,
  input.items,
  input.add_items,
  ctx.statePatch?.cart?.items_added,
  parsedItems,
].filter((a) => Array.isArray(a) && a.length);

const rawItems = candidateLists[0] || [];
const items = rawItems.map((i) => {
  const qty   = num(i.qty ?? i.quantity ?? 1, 1);
  const unit  = num(i.price ?? i.unit ?? i.unit_price ?? 0, 0);
  const name  = String(i.name || i.product || i.title || "item");
  const total = num(i.total, qty * unit);
  const sku   = i.sku ?? null;
  return { name, qty, unit, total, ...(sku ? { sku } : {}) };
});

const subtotal = isOrderPlaced && input.confirmed_subtotal != null
  ? num(input.confirmed_subtotal, 0)
  : items.reduce((s, it) => s + num(it.total, num(it.qty, 0) * num(it.unit, 0)), 0);

out.items_added = items;

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// DUPLICATE ORDER DETECTION (Fix 3)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

function normalizeItemsForCompare(itemList) {
  return JSON.stringify(
    (itemList || [])
      .map(i => ({
        name: String(i.name || "").toLowerCase().trim(),
        qty:  Number(i.qty  || 0),
      }))
      .sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name))
  );
}

function isNewOrder(incomingItems, lastOrderItems, lastOrderStatus, lastOrderTsMs) {
  if (!lastOrderItems?.length) return true;

  const terminalStatuses = ["completed", "delivered", "cancelled", "refunded"];
  if (terminalStatuses.includes(String(lastOrderStatus || "").toLowerCase())) return true;

  // New session if last order > 4 hours ago
  const SESSION_GAP_MS = 4 * 60 * 60 * 1000;
  if (lastOrderTsMs && (Date.now() - Number(lastOrderTsMs)) > SESSION_GAP_MS) return true;

  // Identical items + quantities = duplicate
  const incoming = normalizeItemsForCompare(incomingItems);
  const existing = normalizeItemsForCompare(lastOrderItems);
  if (incoming === existing) return false;

  // Same products, different qty = update to existing order (not new)
  const incomingNames = new Set(
    (incomingItems || []).map(i => String(i.name || "").toLowerCase().trim())
  );
  const existingNames = new Set(
    (lastOrderItems || []).map(i => String(i.name || "").toLowerCase().trim())
  );
  const sameProducts =
    [...incomingNames].every(n => existingNames.has(n)) &&
    [...existingNames].every(n => incomingNames.has(n));

  if (sameProducts) return false;

  // Different products = new order
  return true;
}

const lastOrderCtx    = out.lastSeen?.state?.cart || ctx.state?.cart || {};
const lastOrderItems  = lastOrderCtx.items  || [];
const lastOrderStatus = input.lastOrder?.status || ctx.state?.orderStatus || "open";
const lastOrderTsMs   = input.lastOrder?.lastMessageTs || ctx.lastMessageTs || null;

const orderIsNew       = isNewOrder(items, lastOrderItems, lastOrderStatus, lastOrderTsMs);
const isDuplicateOrder = !orderIsNew && isOrderPlaced;

// Downgrade if duplicate — don't fire another order write
const effectiveIsOrderPlaced = isOrderPlaced && !isDuplicateOrder;

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// ROUTING + ORDER TOUCH DETECTION
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const intentRaw = (out.intent || ctx.intent || "").toLowerCase();
const textLower = (ltext || "").toLowerCase();
const orderTextRe =
  /\b(order|status|track|receipt|invoice|delivery|pickup|cart|checkout|add|buy|purchase|remove|delete|item|items|tray|devai|communion|wafer|wine|shirt|collar|cassock|stole|oil|eliad)\b/;

let nextAction = "reply";
if (ldir === "outbound") nextAction = "await";
else if (ldir === "inbound") {
  if (intentRaw === "order_status")                    nextAction = "orderCheck";
  else if (!intentRaw && orderTextRe.test(textLower))  nextAction = "orderCheck";
  else                                                  nextAction = "reply";
}

// Apply gate overrides in priority order
if (effectiveIsOrderPlaced)    nextAction = "orderPlaced";
if (requiresClarification)     nextAction = "reply";        // must ask clarification question
if (awaitingOrderConfirmation) nextAction = "reply";        // must ask for confirmation

const nextActionRaw  = nextAction;
const nextActionNorm = String(nextActionRaw).trim().toLowerCase();

const orderTouch = !!(
  items.length               ||
  effectiveIsOrderPlaced     ||
  intentRaw === "order_create" ||
  intentRaw === "add_to_cart"  ||
  orderTextRe.test(textLower)
);

out.flags = {
  ...(out.flags || {}),
  orderTouch,
  orderPlaced:                effectiveIsOrderPlaced,
  requiresClarification,
  customerExplicitlyConfirmed,
  awaitingOrderConfirmation,
  isDuplicateOrder,
};
out.orderQueryInput = { wa_id, limit: 1 };

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// SEED order_event
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

const epochSec  = Math.floor((tsMs ?? Date.now()) / 1000);
const sessionId = `${wa_id}_${epochSec}`;
const orderId   = sessionId;

out.order_event = {
  eventType: effectiveIsOrderPlaced
    ? (orderIsNew ? "order.placed" : "order.updated")
    : (items.length ? "order.item.added" : "order.snapshot"),
  status:    orderStatusInput,
  items,
  subtotal,
  tsIso:     nowIso(),
  channel:   "whatsapp",
  source:    "ai_agent",
  sessionId,
  order_id:  orderId,
  isNewOrder: orderIsNew,
  // Gate audit fields
  requiresClarification,
  customerExplicitlyConfirmed,
  isDuplicateOrder,
  // Customer details when order confirmed
  ...(effectiveIsOrderPlaced && input.confirmed_name  ? { customer_name:  input.confirmed_name  } : {}),
  ...(effectiveIsOrderPlaced && input.confirmed_phone ? { customer_phone: input.confirmed_phone } : {}),
};

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// ACTIVITY + CONTEXT PASSTHROUGH
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

out.activity = { ...(input.activity || {}), lastReplyLen: out.reply_text.length };

out.context = {
  ...ctx,
  seenGapMinutes,
  isReturning,
  nextAction:   nextActionRaw,
  nextActionRaw,
  nextActionNorm,
  intent:       intentRaw || null,
  // Gate state — keep alive for next prompt turn
  requiresClarification,
  customerExplicitlyConfirmed,
  awaitingOrderConfirmation,
  isDuplicateOrder,
  // Preserve clarification fields in context.known so prompts
  // continue to show the candidate list on the next turn
  known: {
    ...(ctx.known || {}),
    ...(requiresClarification ? {
      oneQuestionKey:         "item_clarification",
      item:                    ctx.known?.ambiguousRoot         || input.ambiguity?.ambiguousRoot        || "",
      itemCandidates:          ctx.known?.itemCandidates        || input.ambiguity?.candidates           || [],
      ambiguousRoot:           ctx.known?.ambiguousRoot         || input.ambiguity?.ambiguousRoot        || "",
      clarificationQuestion:   ctx.known?.clarificationQuestion || input.ambiguity?.clarificationQuestion || "",
    } : {}),
  },
};

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// ROOT-LEVEL STAMPS
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

out.nextAction      = nextActionRaw;
out.nextActionNorm  = nextActionNorm;
out.wa_id           = wa_id;
out.patch           = { ...(out.patch || {}), wa_id };

out.orderPlaced                = effectiveIsOrderPlaced;
out.order_status               = orderStatusInput;
out.requiresClarification      = requiresClarification;
out.customerExplicitlyConfirmed = customerExplicitlyConfirmed;
out.awaitingOrderConfirmation  = awaitingOrderConfirmation;
out.isDuplicateOrder           = isDuplicateOrder;

if (effectiveIsOrderPlaced) {
  if (input.confirmed_items)            out.confirmed_items    = input.confirmed_items;
  if (input.confirmed_subtotal != null) out.confirmed_subtotal = input.confirmed_subtotal;
  if (input.confirmed_name)             out.confirmed_name     = input.confirmed_name;
  if (input.confirmed_phone)            out.confirmed_phone    = input.confirmed_phone;
}

out.mergeKey = 1;

return [out];

/**
 * getHistory — merges echo-merge-key + existing history
 * Output: { wa_id, history:{ lastInbound, inboundLast5[], outboundLast5[], agentReply }, mergeKey:1 }
 */

function prefer(...v){ return v.find(x => x !== undefined && x !== null && String(x).trim() !== ""); }
function normWa(x){
  if(!x) return "";
  const s = String(x).trim();
  const plus = s.startsWith("+") ? "+" : "";
  const digits = s.replace(/[^\d]/g, "");
  return (plus + digits) || "";
}
function unwrap(v){
  if (v == null || typeof v !== "object") return v;
  if ("stringValue"    in v) return v.stringValue;
  if ("integerValue"   in v) return Number(v.integerValue);
  if ("doubleValue"    in v) return Number(v.doubleValue);
  if ("booleanValue"   in v) return !!v.booleanValue;
  if ("timestampValue" in v) return v.timestampValue;
  if ("mapValue" in v && v.mapValue && v.mapValue.fields) return unwrap(v.mapValue.fields);
  if ("arrayValue" in v && v.arrayValue && Array.isArray(v.arrayValue.values)) return v.arrayValue.values.map(unwrap);
  return v;
}
function toMs(isoOrNum){
  if (isoOrNum == null) return null;
  if (typeof isoOrNum === "number" && Number.isFinite(isoOrNum)) return isoOrNum;
  const t = Date.parse(String(isoOrNum));
  return Number.isFinite(t) ? t : null;
}
function normMsg(m){
  // Accept plain or Firestore-typed
  const f = m && m.fields ? unwrap(m.fields) : m || {};
  const direction = String(f.direction || m.direction || "").toLowerCase();
  const text = String(f.text || m.text || "");
  const tsIso = f.tsIso || m.tsIso || null;
  const tsMs  = (f.tsMs ?? m.tsMs ?? null);
  const ts    = toMs(tsIso) ?? (Number.isFinite(Number(tsMs)) ? Number(tsMs) : null);
  return { direction, text, tsIso: tsIso || (ts ? new Date(ts).toISOString() : null), tsMs: ts };
}
function uniqBy(arr, keyFn){
  const seen = new Set();
  const out = [];
  for (const x of arr) {
    const k = keyFn(x);
    if (!seen.has(k)) { seen.add(k); out.push(x); }
  }
  return out;
}
function takeLastN(arr, n=5){
  return arr
    .filter(x => x && x.tsMs != null && x.direction)
    .sort((a,b) => a.tsMs - b.tsMs)
    .slice(-n);
}

const nowIso = new Date().toISOString();
const nowMs  = Date.now();

// --- wa_id from either lane ---
const wa_id = normWa(prefer(
  $json.wa_id,
  $json?.context?.wa_id,
  $json?.context?.confirm?.phoneCandidate,
  $json?.contacts?.[0]?.wa_id,
  $json?.messages?.[0]?.from
));

// --- gather candidates from BOTH sources ---
let candidates = [];

// 1) echo-merge-key -> messages[]
if (Array.isArray($json?.messages)) {
  candidates.push(...$json.messages.map(normMsg));
}

// 2) echo-merge-key -> context lastInbound/lastOutbound
if ($json?.context?.lastInbound) {
  const i = $json.context.lastInbound;
  candidates.push(normMsg({ direction:"inbound", text:i.text, tsIso:i.tsIso, tsMs:i.tsMs }));
}
if ($json?.context?.lastOutbound) {
  const o = $json.context.lastOutbound;
  candidates.push(normMsg({ direction:"outbound", text:o.text, tsIso:o.tsIso, tsMs:o.tsMs }));
}

// 3) existing upstream history (if present) -> inboundLast5/outboundLast5
if (Array.isArray($json?.history?.inboundLast5)) {
  candidates.push(...$json.history.inboundLast5.map(normMsg));
}
if (Array.isArray($json?.history?.outboundLast5)) {
  candidates.push(...$json.history.outboundLast5.map(normMsg));
}

// dedupe by (direction|tsMs|text)
candidates = uniqBy(
  candidates.filter(Boolean),
  m => `${m.direction}|${m.tsMs || ""}|${m.text.slice(0,80)}`
);

// split and take last 5 each
const inboundLast5  = takeLastN(candidates.filter(m => m.direction === "inbound"), 5);
const outboundLast5 = takeLastN(candidates.filter(m => m.direction === "outbound"), 5);

// compute newest inbound (last element after sort)
const lastInbound = inboundLast5.length ? inboundLast5[inboundLast5.length - 1] : null;

// agent reply from echo-merge-key
const agentText = String(prefer($json.reply_text, $json.output, "")).trim();
const agentReply = agentText ? { direction:"outbound", text:agentText, tsIso: nowIso, tsMs: nowMs } : null;

return [{
  wa_id,
  history: {
    lastInbound,
    inboundLast5,
    outboundLast5,
    agentReply,
  },
  mergeKey: 1,
}];

/**
 * Node: Build Customer History (robust wa_id)
 */

function prefer(...vals) {
  return vals.find(v => v !== undefined && v !== null && String(v).trim() !== "");
}
function normWa(x) {
  if (!x) return "";
  const s = String(x).trim();
  const plus = s.startsWith("+") ? "+" : "";
  const digits = s.replace(/[^\d]/g, "");
  return (plus + digits) || "";
}
const nowIso = new Date().toISOString();
const tiny = (s, n = 140) => String(s || "").replace(/\s+/g, " ").trim().slice(0, n);
const intStr = (n) => ({ integerValue: String(Math.max(0, Number(n || 0))) });
const tsVal = (iso) => ({ timestampValue: new Date(iso || nowIso).toISOString() });
const strVal = (s) => ({ stringValue: String(s || "") });
const boolVal = (b) => ({ booleanValue: !!b });

// ---- Robust wa_id sourcing ----
const waFrom =
  prefer(
    $('getHistory').first().json.wa_id,
    $json?.context?.wa_id,
    $json?.context?.confirm?.phoneCandidate,
    $json?.confirm?.phoneCandidate,
    $json?.phone,
    $json?.contacts?.[0]?.wa_id,
    $json?.messages?.[0]?.from,
    $json?.message?.from
  );

const wa_id = normWa(waFrom);

// If still missing, skip gracefully (don’t throw; prevents flow from failing)
if (!wa_id) {
  return [{
    _skipHistory: true,
    reason: "wa_id not found in payload",
    mergeKey: 1
  }];
}

// ---- Inputs for event detection ----
const inbound  = $json?.context?.lastInbound || null;
const outbound = $json?.context?.lastOutbound || null;
const outText  = $json?.reply_text || outbound?.text || "";
const orderEv  = $json?.order_event || null;

// ---- Event classification ----
let eventType = "chat.snapshot";
let summary   = "message processed";
let lastChat  = null;
let lastOrder = null;
let hasOpenOrder = false;
let lastStatus = "idle";

if (orderEv && orderEv.eventType) {
  eventType = orderEv.eventType;
  summary   = tiny(`${orderEv.eventType} • items=${(orderEv.items||[]).length} • subtotal=${orderEv.subtotal||0}`);
  lastOrder = {
    mapValue: { fields: {
      order_id:  strVal(orderEv.order_id),
      eventType: strVal(orderEv.eventType),
      subtotal:  intStr(orderEv.subtotal || 0),
      tsIso:     tsVal(orderEv.tsIso || nowIso),
    }}
  };
  hasOpenOrder = /order\.item\.added|order\.snapshot/.test(orderEv.eventType) && (orderEv.subtotal || 0) > 0;
  lastStatus = hasOpenOrder ? "order_open" : "order_updated";
} else if (inbound && inbound.direction === "inbound") {
  eventType = "chat.inbound";
  summary   = tiny(inbound.text || "");
  lastStatus = "inbound";
} else if (outbound && outbound.direction === "outbound") {
  eventType = "chat.outbound";
  summary   = tiny(outText || outbound.text || "");
  lastStatus = "outbound";
}

// Pick latest chat pointer
const pickLatest = (...arr) =>
  arr.filter(Boolean).sort((a,b)=> new Date(b.tsIso||0)-new Date(a.tsIso||0))[0];

const latestChat = pickLatest(
  inbound && { direction: "inbound",  tsIso: inbound.tsIso,  preview: tiny(inbound.text||"") },
  outbound && { direction: "outbound", tsIso: outbound.tsIso, preview: tiny(outText||outbound.text||"") }
);

if (latestChat) {
  lastChat = {
    mapValue: { fields: {
      direction: strVal(latestChat.direction),
      tsIso:     tsVal(latestChat.tsIso || nowIso),
      preview:   strVal(latestChat.preview),
    }}
  };
}

// ---- Build Firestore-typed patch ----
const fields = {
  wa_id:       strVal(wa_id),
  updatedAt:   tsVal(nowIso),
  lastSeenIso: tsVal(nowIso),
  status: {
    mapValue: { fields: {
      lastStatus:   strVal(lastStatus),
      hasOpenOrder: boolVal(hasOpenOrder),
    }}
  },
  lastEvent: {
    mapValue: { fields: {
      type:    strVal(eventType),
      tsIso:   tsVal(nowIso),
      summary: strVal(summary),
    }}
  }
};
if (lastChat)  fields.lastChat  = lastChat;
if (lastOrder) fields.lastOrder = lastOrder;

// Optional counters passthrough
const c = $json?.counters;
if (c && typeof c === "object") {
  fields.counts = {
    mapValue: { fields: {
      ordersCreated:    intStr(c.ordersCreated),
      ordersProcessed:  intStr(c.ordersProcessed),
      ordersConcluded:  intStr(c.ordersConcluded),
      paymentsDone:     intStr(c.paymentsDone),
      paymentsPending:  intStr(c.paymentsPending),
    }}
  };
}

// Dynamic updateMask
const historyUpdateMask = Object.keys(fields)
  .map(k => `updateMask.fieldPaths=${encodeURIComponent(k)}`)
  .join("&");

return [{
  wa_id,
  historyPatch: fields,
  historyUpdateMask,
  mergeKey: 1
}];

